Day#06 - Spatial computing

Introduction -
--Spatial Computing is a technology in which digital world combines with the real world by displaying virtual objects into real space instead of screen.
--This also involves the user interacting with this virtual objects 

How does it work? -
--Cameras and sensors visualize and interpret the physical room, tracking objects and human movement in real time.
--It merges data from several inputs like IMU, cameras, etc.
--It then created a live 3D map of the physical space so digital items can anchor to the real surfaces.

Advantages-
--It was a huge milestone for immersive arvr technology.
--It helps in visual learning.
--It is also used in architecture design, interior design, etc.

Real world Example -
--visionOS from Apple is a Spatial computing device.It understands the physical world and make the virtual objects (3D or 2D) anchored in the real space.

